<!-- - Verify before claiming done. Test it, prove it works, then say so -->
<!-- - Prefer working features over documentation -->

<!-- DEFAULT WORKFLOW: brainstorm -> plan -> build -->
<!-- We recommend keeping this unless your team has a good reason to skip steps -->
- Follow the brainstorm, plan, build workflow. Don't jump straight to code
- Brainstorm: explore the problem, discuss approaches, align on direction
- Plan: write a step-by-step implementation outline before touching code
- Build: execute the plan, go back to brainstorming if the approach changes
- For small bug fixes or trivial changes, it's fine to skip straight to building


